                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00/1668: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-29T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 29, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 30—6:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>527. The President has turned over the power to Fausto Navarro Allende, Vice
                    President of the Senate.<note n="8" xml:id="d1006fn8">The Ambassador in Ecuador
                        reported as follows in telegram 529, May 30, 10 a.m.: “Ex-President Arroyo
                        appears to have taken refuge in the Colombian Embassy.” (822.00/1673)</note>
                    This appointment appears to have enraged the opposition. Disturbances in the
                    center of the city appear to be increasing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
